Package: SeqKat
Type: Package
Title: Detection of Kataegis
Version: 0.0.2
Date: 2017-05-04
Author: Fouad Yousif, Xihui Lin, Fan Fan, Christopher Lalansingh
Maintainer: Dr. Paul Boutros <paul.boutros@oicr.on.ca>
Description: Kataegis is a localized hypermutation occurring when a region is enriched in somatic SNVs. Kataegis can result from multiple cytosine deaminations catalyzed by the AID/APOBEC family of proteins. This package contains functions to detect kataegis from SNVs in BED format. SeqKat reports two scores per kataegic event, a hypermutation score and an APOBEC mediated kataegic score. A reference paper will be added upon publication in an upcoming version of this package. Nik-Zainal, Serena et al (2012) <doi:10.1016/j.cell.2012.04.024>
Depends: R (>= 2.15.1), foreach, doParallel
Imports: Rcpp(>= 0.11.0)
LinkingTo: Rcpp
Suggests: testthat, doMC
License: GPL-2
LazyLoad: yes
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
